# React Native Patterns

## Component Structure

```tsx
import React, { useCallback } from 'react';
import { View, StyleSheet } from 'react-native';
import { useTheme } from '@shared/theme';

type Props = {
  title: string;
  amount: number;
  currency: string;
  onPress: () => void;
};

export function TransactionCard({ title, amount, currency, onPress }: Props) {
  const { colors, spacing } = useTheme();

  const handlePress = useCallback(() => {
    onPress();
  }, [onPress]);

  return (
    <View style={[styles.container, { backgroundColor: colors.surface }]}>
      {/* component content */}
    </View>
  );
}

const styles = StyleSheet.create({
  container: {
    borderRadius: 16,
    padding: 16,
  },
});
```

## Rules

- Functional components only, no class components
- Props defined as `type` (not `interface`) colocated above component
- Use `useCallback` for event handlers passed to children
- Use `useMemo` for expensive computations, not for simple values
- StyleSheet.create at bottom of file, never inline styles for repeated elements
- Extract reusable logic into custom hooks prefixed with `use`
- Never use `any` type; use `unknown` with type guards when needed
- Every component must handle: loading, empty, error, and success states

## Navigation

- Use typed navigation with `NativeStackScreenProps` and `BottomTabScreenProps`
- Define all route params in `src/presentation/navigation/types.ts`
- Screen components receive route params via `route.params`

## Performance

- Use `React.memo` for list item components
- Use `FlashList` from @shopify/flash-list instead of FlatList for large lists
- Avoid anonymous functions in JSX for frequently re-rendered components
- Use WatermelonDB's `withObservables` or `useObservable` for reactive data
- Implement skeleton loading for every data-dependent screen

## Accessibility

- Every touchable element needs `accessibilityLabel` and `accessibilityRole`
- Minimum touch target size: 44x44 points
- Support dynamic font scaling
- Color contrast ratio must meet WCAG AA (4.5:1 for text)
